{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"property","remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"centerOffset","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to zero and its "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","title":"MapLibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"kind":"symbol","title":"centerOffset","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}]}}}